						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab set up near the Jaṭṭiṅgarāya temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1111.</p>						

						<p>This record which is dated <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 37, Khara, Pushya, Puṇṇame, Friday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti,</hi> stops abruptly after giving the date. The details of the date are irregular. The given <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1111, December 17, Sunday,</hi> whereas the <hi rend="italic">saṁkrānti</hi> occurred on Monday, December 25, the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> being ba. 8. The record falls in the reign-period of Vikramāditya VI.</p>						

						</summary>
